      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AKINA ROCKY (6) got around the 435m at Sale to take a Grade 5 in a decent 24.51 for a 2.75 lengths success. Can measure up again if runs up to latest time. ELEVATE (8) crossed over from out wide but caught the leaders turning before drawing clear to score (25.75) at Ballarat in a Grade 5 over 450m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Leading chance again. JUMBUK JOZEF (2) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Traralgon behind Top Kade (20.30) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Comes through a solid form race last start. Hard to beat again. TO PERU (3) missed the placings when well backed last time but cannot be taken lightly.",
